      "narrative": "An outdoor enclosure housing one grey-winged trumpeter and a second outdoor enclosure housing two Stanley cranes\ndid not provide adequate shade to these birds at time of inspection. Enclosures with insufficient shade for the birds may\npotentially cause overheating or discomfort. Primary enclosures must be constructed and maintained so that they provide\nsufficient shade to comfortably shelter all birds housed in the primary enclosure at one time, including low ranking birds\nthat are maintained in social groupings that form dominance hierarchies.\nCorrect by 04/10/2026.\nThis inspection and exit interview were conducted with facility representatives.\nAdditional Inspectors:\nGeoffrey Olsen, VETERINARY MEDICAL OFFICER\nLouis Divincenti n"
    }
  ],
  "narrative": "3.153(a)(1)(vii) \n   \nPrimary enclosures. \nAn outdoor enclosure housing one grey-winged trumpeter and a second outdoor enclosure housing two Stanley cranes \ndid not provide adequate shade to these birds at time of inspection. Enclosures with insufficient shade for the birds may \npotentially cause overheating or discomfort. Primary enclosures must be constructed and maintained so that they provide \nsufficient shade to comfortably shelter all birds housed in the primary enclosure at one time, including low ranking birds \nthat are maintained in social groupings that form dominance hierarchies. \n \nCorrect by 04/10/2026. \n \nThis inspection and exit interview were conducted with facility representatives. \n \nAdditional Inspectors: \nGeoffrey Olsen, VETERINARY MEDICAL OFFICER \nLouis Divincenti n",
